Adrenaline (epinephrine) is commonly used in CPCR according to the AHA 2010 guidelines, as evidenced by articles discussing its administration frequency during resuscitation. Atropine was discussed mainly within the context of AV block treatments rather than CPCR. Therefore, it seems unlikely to see Atropine being part of the standard protocol in CPCR.
